Dialogue: 99,0:00:02.82,0:00:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And now for my report if I may.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:06.99,0:00:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We just received word of the Emperor\Nof Earthwold's sudden passing.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:11.12,0:00:16.29,default 2,,0,0,0,,And there is now a power struggle\Nwithin the imperial palace.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:16.29,0:00:20.21,default 2,,0,0,0,,The emperor's charisma is what\Npropelled the empire forward.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:20.21,0:00:23.92,default 2,,0,0,0,,But the brighter the light, the\Ndeeper the darkness that follows.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:23.92,0:00:28.26,default 2,,0,0,0,,It will be even darker if they\Nfailed to name a successor.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:28.26,0:00:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There is unrest within the empire\Nand the kingdoms surrounding us.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:33.10,0:00:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we are—\NOr should I say, here in Natra,
Dialogue: 99,0:00:37.18,0:00:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we are graced with a beacon of hope.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:39.64,0:00:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince Wein, that would\Nbe you, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:43.94,0:00:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not just me.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:45.52,0:00:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You liegemen who supported\Nmy father all these years
Dialogue: 99,0:00:48.61,0:00:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are also a beacon of hope.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:51.24,0:00:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:52.53,0:00:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not worthy of such words.
Dialogue: 99,0:00:56.87,0:01:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we stand united\Ntoward the same goal,
Dialogue: 99,0:01:00.58,0:01:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no challenge we can't overcome.
Dialogue: 99,0:01:03.13,0:01:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That earlier matter with the\Nimperial ambassador proves it.
Dialogue: 99,0:01:07.67,0:01:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It is just as you say, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:01:10.13,0:01:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness, what a\Nmagnificent man you've become.
Dialogue: 99,0:01:13.64,0:01:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else to report?
Dialogue: 99,0:01:15.30,0:01:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing more.
Dialogue: 99,0:01:16.35,0:01:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I thank you. You're dismissed.
Dialogue: 99,0:01:19.23,0:01:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:01:35.37,0:01:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,2317)\}I can't wait to sell off this kingdom!
Dialogue: 99,0:03:25.98,0:03:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're also a beacon of hope?
Dialogue: 99,0:03:29.69,0:03:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we stand united\Ntoward the same goal?
Dialogue: 99,0:03:33.48,0:03:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean a word of it!
Dialogue: 99,0:03:35.11,0:03:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No way in hell can I get this\Nkingdom out of the mess it's in!
Dialogue: 99,0:03:38.70,0:03:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't gonna happen! No way, no how!
Dialogue: 99,0:03:42.70,0:03:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't keep saying such\Nthings, even if you're joking, Wein.
Dialogue: 99,0:03:47.96,0:03:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I never said I was joking,\NNinym! I'm totally serious!
Dialogue: 99,0:03:52.42,0:03:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's even worse.
Dialogue: 99,0:03:54.26,0:03:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You grow lazy the moment\Nyou know no one's watching.
Dialogue: 99,0:03:57.55,0:03:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You must try a little harder.
Dialogue: 99,0:03:59.76,0:04:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's with the poindexter act?
Dialogue: 99,0:04:04.68,0:04:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninym, even you know how dirt poor\Nthis kingdom is in every possible way.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:11.40,0:04:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're a petty kingdom with no\Nmore than 500,000 subjects.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:15.07,0:04:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the continent's far north,\Nspring is short, and winter is long.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:20.20,0:04:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, most of our territory consists\Nof barren rock and mountains.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:23.87,0:04:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no money to invest\Nin domestic development,
Dialogue: 99,0:04:26.58,0:04:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,our meager resources mean\Nwe can't raise capital,
Dialogue: 99,0:04:29.37,0:04:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have no industries of value.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:32.29,0:04:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's putting it lightly.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:34.00,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We're a weak little kingdom that\Ncould be wiped off the map in a flash.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:37.92,0:04:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And now my old man's fallen\Nill, and I gotta run things.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:41.55,0:04:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take it anymore!
Dialogue: 99,0:04:44.93,0:04:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to sell this\Nkingdom and disappear.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:49.44,0:04:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But to do that, first I\Ngotta strengthen Natra.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:53.15,0:04:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The greater a nation's value, the\Nhigher the price it will fetch.
Dialogue: 99,0:04:57.94,0:05:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That will affect how cushy\Nmy retirement life will be!
Dialogue: 99,0:05:02.16,0:05:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, I'm sick of hearing\Nthat harebrained plan.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:05.45,0:05:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other things you\Nshould be worrying about.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:11.21,0:05:14.92,default 2,,0,0,0,,Dear Brother, sorry to bother\Nyou when you're so busy.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:14.92,0:05:17.25,default 2,,0,0,0,,Do you have a moment?
Dialogue: 99,0:05:17.25,0:05:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:21.01,0:05:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something the matter, Falanya?
Dialogue: 99,0:05:23.18,0:05:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I just saw Father and wished to\Ninform you of his condition.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:27.47,0:05:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:28.27,0:05:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Father is looking much better.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:31.77,0:05:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He even felt ready to take a walk today.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:34.10,0:05:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great news.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:36.02,0:05:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's hold off on\Nthat walk a bit longer.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:39.36,0:05:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 99,0:05:40.82,0:05:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The neighboring kingdom of Marden is\Npoised to invade Natra at any moment.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:45.95,0:05:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Are you saying...?
Dialogue: 99,0:05:48.20,0:05:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to war.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:51.42,0:05:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Marden was once on par with Natra
Dialogue: 99,0:05:54.71,0:05:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,until a newly discovered gold mine\Nallowed their kingdom to rapidly expand.
Dialogue: 99,0:05:58.34,0:06:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However, their current king is unpopular.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:01.51,0:06:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But you already know that.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:03.30,0:06:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:04.30,0:06:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned he is served\Nby corrupt officials
Dialogue: 99,0:06:07.26,0:06:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,who ignore his failures and reaffirm his\Nbelief that he's an enlightened ruler.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:12.64,0:06:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He is creating a vicious cycle that will\Ndrive his kingdom into the ground.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:18.23,0:06:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why their king is looking for\Nan easy win to distract his people.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:22.95,0:06:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And our kingdom fits the bill
Dialogue: 99,0:06:25.66,0:06:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,now that the imperial forces that\Nwere stationed here are gone.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:29.20,0:06:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But you won't let them do that, will you?
Dialogue: 99,0:06:33.37,0:06:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I overheard the military officers\Ntalking in the inner courtyard.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:37.92,0:06:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What did they say?
Dialogue: 99,0:06:39.21,0:06:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"Now is the time for the swords of\NNatra to fulfill their appointed task!"
Dialogue: 99,0:06:43.38,0:06:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And, "As liegemen, we must live\Nup to the prince's expectations."
Dialogue: 99,0:06:47.39,0:06:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Stuff like that!
Dialogue: 99,0:06:48.26,0:06:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they really?
Dialogue: 99,0:06:49.89,0:06:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard them, too, right, Nanaki?
Dialogue: 99,0:06:54.10,0:06:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they wouldn't shut up.
Dialogue: 99,0:06:56.69,0:07:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh no, are those idiots getting all\Nexcited at the thought of battle?
Dialogue: 99,0:07:00.44,0:07:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are they raring to go?
Dialogue: 99,0:07:02.69,0:07:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Do they have any idea how\Nexpensive it is to wage war?!
Dialogue: 99,0:07:06.82,0:07:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Dearest?
Dialogue: 99,0:07:09.99,0:07:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pray for your victory.\NThat's all I can do.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:14.20,0:07:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,May you defeat our foes!
Dialogue: 99,0:07:16.54,0:07:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, thanks.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:18.29,0:07:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll launch a half-hearted\Nattack and then sue for peace.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:32.81,0:07:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Natra's forces number 6,000\Nagainst Marden's 7,000.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:37.27,0:07:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:38.90,0:07:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Both armies are arrayed on the field.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:41.61,0:07:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we wait for the battle to begin.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:44.53,0:07:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:45.78,0:07:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was hoping
Dialogue: 99,0:07:47.78,0:07:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you might have some words for the troops.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:50.99,0:07:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Battles wear down more\Nthan a soldier's body.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:54.12,0:07:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They also take a toll on his soul.
Dialogue: 99,0:07:56.87,0:08:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you not give them a few\Nwords to boost their morale?
Dialogue: 99,0:08:01.92,0:08:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Though they've been trained by the empire,
Dialogue: 99,0:08:04.38,0:08:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,their tension is palpable, for\Nthis is their first real battle.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:11.72,0:08:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Torace of Heinoy.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:14.52,0:08:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your spear is upside down.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:18.35,0:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me, Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:08:22.02,0:08:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Karlmann, Patess,
Dialogue: 99,0:08:23.69,0:08:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Livi, Logli.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:25.53,0:08:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that funny.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:27.36,0:08:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:08:29.95,0:08:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That eased the tension a bit.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:34.54,0:08:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Until this day, Natra's army has\Nbeen looked down on as weak.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:39.37,0:08:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It may have been true at one time.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:42.46,0:08:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Marden's army likely\Nlooks down on us, too.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:46.67,0:08:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But I know the truth.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:48.76,0:08:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You have survived the\Nmost grueling training.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:52.64,0:08:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you possess a noble\Ncourage that is beyond compare.
Dialogue: 99,0:08:57.72,0:09:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know that as you face our invaders,\Na flame imperishable burns in your hearts.
Dialogue: 99,0:09:04.94,0:09:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you can no longer be\Nseen as weak by any measure.
Dialogue: 99,0:09:12.41,0:09:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now prove it in battle!
Dialogue: 99,0:09:14.87,0:09:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Show them that we are\Nthe dragon of the north!
Dialogue: 99,0:09:17.74,0:09:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let it resound across the continent! We\Nare the most formidable force of all!
Dialogue: 99,0:09:22.37,0:09:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is the day we fight\Nand rewrite history!
Dialogue: 99,0:09:33.97,0:09:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That was magnificent.
Dialogue: 99,0:09:35.80,0:09:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At least they won't be so nervous\Nthat they lose hold of their weapons.
Dialogue: 99,0:09:40.43,0:09:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you plant those soldiers\Nyou addressed by name?
Dialogue: 99,0:09:45.36,0:09:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly. I was winging it.
Dialogue: 99,0:09:48.69,0:09:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not an empire with hundreds\Nof thousands of troops.
Dialogue: 99,0:09:51.74,0:09:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Natra only has about 10,000\Nif you add them all up.
Dialogue: 99,0:10:12.13,0:10:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear me, brave warriors of Marden!
Dialogue: 99,0:10:15.59,0:10:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Natra's troops are but\Nlowly foot soldiers!
Dialogue: 99,0:10:18.56,0:10:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They mistake recklessness for courage
Dialogue: 99,0:10:20.81,0:10:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and are now trying to thwart our\Nadvance like the fools they are.
Dialogue: 99,0:10:24.90,0:10:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is no way in hell\Nthese northern peasants
Dialogue: 99,0:10:28.61,0:10:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,can defeat our army of elite troops!
Dialogue: 99,0:10:33.82,0:10:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Trample them underfoot!
Dialogue: 99,0:10:35.36,0:10:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Stain this wasteland red with their blood!
Dialogue: 99,0:10:42.16,0:10:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand ready, men!
Dialogue: 99,0:10:48.04,0:10:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready...
Dialogue: 99,0:10:49.92,0:10:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:02.35,0:11:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a report, Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:04.23,0:11:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Marden's troops are in a\Ncenter-heavy formation!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:07.90,0:11:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll break through their center, then\Nturn and crush them from behind!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:13.28,0:11:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, we'll stand our ground!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:15.86,0:11:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll break upon our defensive line.
Dialogue: 99,0:11:18.03,0:11:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mardenian army won't\Nknow what hit them!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:30.54,0:11:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:32.75,0:11:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a second. What is happening?
Dialogue: 99,0:11:35.26,0:11:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,General Urgio! Our left flank\Nis requesting reinforcements!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:39.05,0:11:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! Sanse Company was decimated!\NTology Company is moving to fill the void!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:43.22,0:11:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,General! Our right flank\Nis in dire straits, too!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:46.18,0:11:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What the hell?! How can these\NNatran troops be so formidable?!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:50.56,0:11:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How can Marden be so weak?!
Dialogue: 99,0:11:53.82,0:11:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is going on? How can we\Npossibly be kicking their butt?
Dialogue: 99,0:12:03.29,0:12:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with Marden's tactics?\NIt's not a schoolyard brawl!
Dialogue: 99,0:12:07.07,0:12:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, our troops are dominating.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:10.13,0:12:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a problem, Your Highness?
Dialogue: 99,0:12:12.59,0:12:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's just I'm surprised by how\Nfiercely our troops are fighting.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:16.42,0:12:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Has it all not gone as you\Nplanned, Your Highness?
Dialogue: 99,0:12:20.64,0:12:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that day you met\Nwith the imperial ambassador.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:26.43,0:12:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ambassador Brandel.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:27.98,0:12:32.77,default 2,,0,0,0,,I view maintaining relations with\Nthe empire as my top priority.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:32.77,0:12:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As such, should we not bridge the divide
Dialogue: 99,0:12:35.23,0:12:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,between the Imperial Army\Nand Natra's Royal Army?
Dialogue: 99,0:12:39.53,0:12:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I concur, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:41.07,0:12:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What I propose is this.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:42.53,0:12:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you not provide the Imperial Army's\Nexpertise and funding to our Royal Army?
Dialogue: 99,0:12:49.79,0:12:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would ever believe they\Nwould accept such a request?
Dialogue: 99,0:12:55.13,0:12:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But Ambassador Brandel {\i1}did{\i0} accept it.
Dialogue: 99,0:12:58.88,0:13:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we've adopted the methods of\Nthe continent's greatest military force.
Dialogue: 99,0:13:04.18,0:13:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that our military has tapped\Nthe empire's abundant capital,
Dialogue: 99,0:13:08.06,0:13:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's grown more powerful before our eyes.
Dialogue: 99,0:13:10.60,0:13:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Natra's army is more than a match
Dialogue: 99,0:13:12.73,0:13:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for any petty kingdom that has only\Nexperienced limited skirmishes.
Dialogue: 99,0:13:17.73,0:13:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ideally, Marden will cut\Ntheir losses and run, but...
Dialogue: 99,0:13:23.24,0:13:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness! The center of\Nour line is under pressure!
Dialogue: 99,0:13:28.08,0:13:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The morale of our forces\Nis starting to fray.
Dialogue: 99,0:13:30.96,0:13:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Crap!
Dialogue: 99,0:13:32.71,0:13:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,After all that training?
Dialogue: 99,0:13:34.79,0:13:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after rigorous training\Nand your inspiring words,
Dialogue: 99,0:13:38.26,0:13:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Natra's troops are not mentally\Nprepared for a real battlefield.
Dialogue: 99,0:13:43.55,0:13:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The chill air, splattering blood, and\Nwanton slaughter consume them.
Dialogue: 99,0:13:51.40,0:13:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The tide turns against us.
Dialogue: 99,0:13:55.73,0:13:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please don't notice.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:02.24,0:14:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Natra's forces are no\Nlonger pressing the attack.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:05.32,0:14:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Their strength is but a facade.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:08.58,0:14:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the commanders of\Nboth flanks to enter the fray
Dialogue: 99,0:14:13.04,0:14:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and stop the enemy dead in their tracks!
Dialogue: 99,0:14:16.04,0:14:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And have our forces in the\Ncenter reform their lines!
Dialogue: 99,0:14:19.59,0:14:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We strike once they are ready!
Dialogue: 99,0:14:21.76,0:14:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the target?
Dialogue: 99,0:14:24.51,0:14:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The head of their leader!
Dialogue: 99,0:14:31.35,0:14:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, crap!
Dialogue: 99,0:14:32.89,0:14:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He noticed.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:34.64,0:14:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness, we must fall back now.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:37.31,0:14:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:39.36,0:14:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,General! They're fleeing from their camp!
Dialogue: 99,0:14:42.61,0:14:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Pathetic. It's better to\Nfall bravely in battle.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:47.66,0:14:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Take them from behind before\Nthey can hide in the hills.
Dialogue: 99,0:14:53.63,0:14:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Damnit. How did this happen?
Dialogue: 99,0:14:56.83,0:14:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly, men, turnabout!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:02.59,0:15:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They've accepted their fate!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:12.47,0:15:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Archers, loose!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:17.35,0:15:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is looking like a complete victory!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:26.11,0:15:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's this?!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,An ambush?!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:30.58,0:15:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They're attacking!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:31.74,0:15:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Defend General Urgio with your lives!
Dialogue: 99,0:15:34.62,0:15:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Pathetic.
Dialogue: 99,0:15:47.13,0:15:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why you—
Dialogue: 99,0:15:49.85,0:15:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the general, I take it?
Dialogue: 99,0:15:51.93,0:15:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender now, and you may\Nsurvive with prompt treatment.
Dialogue: 99,0:15:56.52,0:15:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender? Surrender, you say?
Dialogue: 99,0:15:59.90,0:16:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,To hell with that!
Dialogue: 99,0:16:01.27,0:16:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the general of Marden's army!
Dialogue: 99,0:16:03.27,0:16:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not gonna surrender to some woman,\Nand a lowly, dirty Flahm at that!
Dialogue: 99,0:16:08.20,0:16:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So be it.
Dialogue: 99,0:16:15.37,0:16:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Take his head and raise\Nit high for all to see.
Dialogue: 99,0:16:18.71,0:16:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And see that his last words\Nare never heard again.
Dialogue: 99,0:16:23.55,0:16:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 99,0:16:25.01,0:16:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy general died in\Nsilence as far as I'm concerned.
Dialogue: 99,0:16:46.45,0:16:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This battle's pretty much over.
Dialogue: 99,0:16:49.45,0:16:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 99,0:16:50.82,0:16:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now what the hell am I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 99,0:16:57.08,0:17:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we've crushed\Nthe Mardenian invaders,
Dialogue: 99,0:17:00.46,0:17:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Eastern Marden is utterly exposed!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:03.42,0:17:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We should turn the tables\Nand invade at once!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:07.76,0:17:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We could carve off a large\Nchunk of their territory!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:12.30,0:17:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 99,0:17:13.34,0:17:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Our swift victory means we still\Nhave plenty of troops and supplies.
Dialogue: 99,0:17:18.31,0:17:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:19.23,0:17:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your command?!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:22.19,0:17:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't believe this!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:23.94,0:17:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Do they have any idea how risky it is to\Ninvade without carefully planning?!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:29.11,0:17:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But how can I possibly say that now?
Dialogue: 99,0:17:31.91,0:17:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now that we've utterly\Ncrushed Marden's army,
Dialogue: 99,0:17:34.66,0:17:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}weak-kneed words will cause my generals'\Nloyalty to crash down like an avalanche.
Dialogue: 99,0:17:40.46,0:17:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And that can only end in a coup d'etat!
Dialogue: 99,0:17:44.58,0:17:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I didn't want to do this,\Nbut I've got no choice.
Dialogue: 99,0:17:48.92,0:17:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear what you're saying.
Dialogue: 99,0:17:51.17,0:17:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're correct in saying our great victory\Nhas put tremendous momentum behind us.
Dialogue: 99,0:17:57.68,0:18:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I propose this.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:01.14,0:18:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, ours is a\Nbarren, unprosperous land.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:05.06,0:18:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But the same can be said of Marden.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:09.11,0:18:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And its eastern region\Nhas few strategic points.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:12.32,0:18:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on our current troop strength\Nand places within our grasp,
Dialogue: 99,0:18:16.78,0:18:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,there {\i1}is{\i0} a location worth taking.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:20.37,0:18:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jilaat Gold Mine.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:22.46,0:18:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're to capture\Nanything, it should be that.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:27.46,0:18:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes! That's the reaction I wanted.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:30.13,0:18:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After all, targeting their\Ngold mine is crazy talk!
Dialogue: 99,0:18:33.38,0:18:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No matter how much strategic value it has,
Dialogue: 99,0:18:35.89,0:18:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}attacking without much intel and\Nwith troops weary from battle
Dialogue: 99,0:18:41.64,0:18:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}would be fruitless, futile, feckless.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:45.56,0:18:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it has stoked a serious debate.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:48.44,0:18:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The gold mine is impossible,\Nso they need another target.
Dialogue: 99,0:18:52.11,0:18:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But where? Does Eastern\NMarden have another location
Dialogue: 99,0:18:55.24,0:18:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with the strategic value of the mine?
Dialogue: 99,0:18:57.49,0:18:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No! No, it doesn't!
Dialogue: 99,0:18:59.49,0:19:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There are no other targets of value!
Dialogue: 99,0:19:01.91,0:19:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The other possibilities are worthless.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:04.29,0:19:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The moment they realize that, their\Nthirst for conquests will vanish.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:09.13,0:19:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They may think a bit less of me for\Nmaking a ludicrous proposal,
Dialogue: 99,0:19:12.76,0:19:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but I'm used to it!
Dialogue: 99,0:19:14.09,0:19:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And it'll be totally worth it\Nif they decide to withdraw!
Dialogue: 99,0:19:18.55,0:19:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:19.43,0:19:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here it comes!
Dialogue: 99,0:19:22.02,0:19:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well? Tell me my proposal is crazy talk.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:25.64,0:19:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They want to tell me how reckless\Nit is, but they don't know how.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:29.23,0:19:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I gotta think of a way for my\Nofficers to preserve their honor
Dialogue: 99,0:19:32.23,0:19:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}by acting like their wisdom\Nstruck deep into my soul.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:36.45,0:19:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I do that, everything will be—
Dialogue: 99,0:19:38.07,0:19:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I am in awe of your intellect.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:41.66,0:19:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What?!
Dialogue: 99,0:19:42.62,0:19:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It is just as you say, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:44.91,0:19:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jilaat Gold Mine is\Nthe only target of worth!
Dialogue: 99,0:19:48.12,0:19:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is, indeed, a surprise.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:50.08,0:19:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly believe that your Highness
Dialogue: 99,0:19:52.75,0:19:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,knew of our long-standing\Nplan to take the gold mine.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:56.30,0:19:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm absolutely speechless.
Dialogue: 99,0:19:58.59,0:20:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wait, what?!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:01.05,0:20:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,While we were celebrating our victory,
Dialogue: 99,0:20:03.72,0:20:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness must have been\Nstudying the feasibility of our plan.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:07.73,0:20:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm humbled by your foresight.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:11.48,0:20:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness, we'll set out at\Nonce upon your command!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:14.57,0:20:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us strike the gold\Nmine while the iron's hot!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:17.49,0:20:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:18.24,0:20:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Highness!\NYour Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:19.20,0:20:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1695,1016\}Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:19.20,0:20:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1216,1016\}Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:19.20,0:20:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,1016\}Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:19.20,0:20:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(235,1016\}Your Highness!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:23.91,0:20:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ninym, help.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:26.04,0:20:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sorry. Nothing I can do.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:33.09,0:20:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The invasion of Marden is a done deal.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:36.67,0:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I could've nixed the plan if our\Narmy hadn't won by a landslide.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:42.05,0:20:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So what now, Wein?
Dialogue: 99,0:20:43.93,0:20:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna think\Nabout it. I can't even.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:46.93,0:20:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that's not an option.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:48.94,0:20:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not?
Dialogue: 99,0:20:50.14,0:20:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:51.27,0:20:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll think of something\Nif you meow like a cat.
Dialogue: 99,0:20:55.82,0:20:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, come on then!
Dialogue: 99,0:20:57.32,0:20:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Cat got your tongue, Ninym?
Dialogue: 99,0:20:59.57,0:21:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Has curiosity killed your inner cat?
Dialogue: 99,0:21:01.95,0:21:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Too proud to channel your inner feline?
Dialogue: 99,0:21:06.33,0:21:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,1016\}Fine.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:08.04,0:21:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1061.5,1016\}Fine. Meow.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:10.75,0:21:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what's the plan?
Dialogue: 99,0:21:12.83,0:21:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:13.96,0:21:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We should start by verifying the\Nintel on the mine's defenses.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:18.30,0:21:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we should reassess our supply lines
Dialogue: 99,0:21:20.76,0:21:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and do our best to maintain troop morale.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:23.51,0:21:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We can take the mine before Marden\Ncan mount an adequate defense.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:27.72,0:21:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's all easier said than done.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:32.77,0:21:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Meow.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:34.15,0:21:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. It's back-to-back battles\Nafter the Polta Wastelands.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:38.03,0:21:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're bound to stumble somewhere.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:40.65,0:21:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But that stumble is just what we need\Nto convince our army to withdraw.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:46.28,0:21:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we wait for that to happen.
Dialogue: 98,0:21:47.87,0:21:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(,1464,1009.5)\fscx60\fscy60\bord2.7\shad1.3}Meow.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:49.16,0:21:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:51.75,0:21:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Meow.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:55.59,0:21:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that didn't work.
Dialogue: 99,0:21:57.88,0:22:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We actually took the mine.
Dialogue: 99,0:22:00.21,0:22:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We actually took it.
Dialogue: 99,0:22:04.26,0:22:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, meow for me.
Dialogue: 99,0:22:06.85,0:22:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so over that.
